# ZurichJS Conference — Cursor AI Rules

The canonical AI-agent rulebook is **[CLAUDE.md](./CLAUDE.md)** at the repo root.
Scoped guidance lives in nested `CLAUDE.md` files in each major directory.

Cursor: read `CLAUDE.md` first, then the nearest scoped `CLAUDE.md` for the directory
you're working in.

## Quick reference

- **Package manager:** pnpm 11 (never npm/yarn). **Node 22**.
- **Linter:** oxlint (not ESLint). `pnpm lint`.
- **Tests:** Vitest. `pnpm test:related <files>` for fast iteration.
- **Framework:** Next.js 15 Pages Router (not App Router).
- **Imports:** use `@/*` (alias for `src/*`). No relative `../../` chains.
- **Types:** strict TypeScript, no `any`. Domain types in `src/lib/types/`. Never hand-edit `database.generated.ts`.
- **Components:** Atomic Design (atoms → molecules → organisms). Barrel exports. Files < 500 LOC.
- **State:** TanStack Query for server, Context for UI, nuqs for URL.
- **Validation:** Zod everywhere on API inputs.
- **Logging:** `logger.scope('Name')` — never `console.log`.
- **Auth:** three patterns in API routes — see `src/pages/api/CLAUDE.md`.
- **Pre-commit:** slow; never bypass with `--no-verify`.

## Where things live

| Need | Read |
|---|---|
| API route patterns + auth | `src/pages/api/CLAUDE.md` |
| CFP business logic | `src/lib/cfp/CLAUDE.md` |
| Supabase clients (RLS!) | `src/lib/supabase/CLAUDE.md` |
| Stripe + webhooks | `src/lib/stripe/CLAUDE.md` |
| Components (a11y, motion) | `src/components/CLAUDE.md` |
| Custom hooks | `src/hooks/CLAUDE.md` |
| Migrations + RLS | `supabase/migrations/CLAUDE.md` |
| Domain types | `src/lib/types/CLAUDE.md` |
| Zod schemas | `src/lib/validations/CLAUDE.md` |
| Analytics events | `src/lib/analytics/CLAUDE.md` |
| Email templates | `src/emails/CLAUDE.md` |
| Static content | `src/data/CLAUDE.md` |

For accessibility, framer-motion, and hydration patterns, see the relevant scoped
`CLAUDE.md` files — those rules used to live here and have been moved to where they apply.
